:QUOTE
Your truck is a billboard. Your uniform is a handshake. Brand everything.

:INFO
Landscaping Business Brand from Scratch
Build a cohesive brand identity for a landscaping business that works on a truck door, a T-shirt, a yard sign, and a website. Start with a name and color palette and apply consistently.

:COUNTER.half
$500
Realistic budget for logo, cards, and yard signs
|
:COUNTER.half
3 Colors
Maximum for a clean, reproducible brand palette

:PATH
Choose the Name
Pick a name that is easy to spell, easy to say, and works as a domain. Avoid generic names like Green Thumb or ABC Landscaping. Include your town or your own name for local trust and searchability.

:PATH
Build the Visual Identity
Hire a designer on 99designs or Fiverr for a logo. Specify your color palette in hex codes for print and digital consistency. Get files in SVG, PNG, and PDF so you can use them anywhere.

:PATH
Apply the Brand
Wrap or magnetically brand your truck. Order embroidered shirts and hats. Print yard signs for completed jobs with permission. Apply the logo to invoices, estimates, and your Google Business Profile.

:CHECKLIST
Brand Launch Checklist
[ ] Shortlist 5 business names and check domain availability
[ ] Register your .com domain immediately after deciding
[ ] Brief a logo designer with your name, colors, and vibe
[ ] Order 500 business cards with QR code linking to your site
[ ] Buy 10 yard signs for completed job placements
[ ] Get 5 embroidered shirts for crew uniforms
[ ] Apply logo to your Google Business Profile and social headers

:NOTE
Brand consistency is more important than brand perfection. A simple logo used everywhere beats an elaborate one used inconsistently. Start shipping branded materials before you feel ready.
